{"name":"Badger","size":"small","type":"humanoid","tag":"goblin","alignment":"chaotic evil","hitDice":"","armorName":"mage armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":7,"otherArmorDesc":"10","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"230 (20d8 + 60)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"12","dexPoints":"18","conPoints":"16","intPoints":"12","wisPoints":"16","chaPoints":"22","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"30","telepathy":60,"cr":"22","customCr":"1 (200 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":false,"legendariesDescription":"The monster can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The monster regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the monster can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the monster can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The monster can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the monster's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the monster's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the monster dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Alert","desc":"Badger gains a +5 bonus to initiative. He also can't be surprised while he is conscious, and other creatures don't gain advantage on attack rolls against him as a result of being unseen by him."},{"name":"Indescribable Form","desc":"Badger's form is no longer bound by the laws of reality. As an action, you can choose to appear as any creature or object that is Small or Medium, such as a dog, a mass of floating lights, an idealized version of yourself, or a simple wooden crate. No matter what appearance you chose, your statistics and capacity for action are the same. This appearance is a physical change, but magic that allows others to discern the true form of shapeshifters will reveal your normal appearance. This appearance lasts until you choose to change it again."},{"name":"Innate Spellcasting","desc":"Badger's innate spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell save DC [CHA SAVE], [CHA ATK] to hit with spell attacks). It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:\n\n> At will: _arcane eye, detect magic, detect thoughts, invisibility, levitate, mage armor, silent image, speak with animals, speak with dead_"},{"name":"Lucky","desc":"Badger has three luck points. Whenever he makes an attack roll, an ability check, or a saving throw, he can spend one luck point to roll an additional d20. He can choose which of the d20s is used for the attack roll, ability check, or saving throw. He can also spend one luck point when an attack is made against him. He regains expended luck points when he finishes a long rest."},{"name":"War Caster","desc":"Badger has advantage on Constitution saving throws that he makes to maintain concentration on a spell when he takes damage. He can cast when having his hands occupied. He can cast spells for opportunity attacks, as long as the spell has a casting time of 1 action."}],"actions":[{"name":"Eldritch Annihilation","desc":"_Ranged Spell Attack:_ Five beams of eldritch energy streak towards creatures within range. [CHA ATK] to hit, range 300/1200 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [CHA 1D10] force damage per beam. Badger can allow each beam to do one of the following:\n- Move the creature hit up to 10 feet closer to him.\n- Push the creature hit up to 10 feet away from him.\n- Reduce the hit creature's speed by 10 feet until the end of your next turn.\n- Damage a secondary target within 5 feet of the primary target, at the expense of 1d4 hit points.\n- Cast fireball as a bonus action centered on the creature hit.\n\nBadger can also expend a bonus action before casting to empower the eldritch annihilation with the following:\n**Doom**: Channel all energy into one location. Target only one creature that must succeed on a DC [CHA SAVE] Charisma saving throw or be struck by all beams. If the attack kills the creature, Badger can empower his next Eldritch Annihilation to be Doom.\n**Destruction**: Unleash a web of eldritch energy. Target one creature and up to six other creatures within 30 feet of the primary target. Each secondary target must succeed a DC [CHA SAVE] Wisdom saving throw or be struck by the one beam of the blast. The primary target is truck by a number of beams equal to the number of creatures who failed their saving throw."}],"bonusActions":[],"reactions":[],"legendaries":[],"mythics":[],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"wis","order":4},{"name":"cha","order":5}],"skills":[{"name":"arcana","stat":"int"},{"name":"deception","stat":"cha","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"insight","stat":"wis"},{"name":"intimidation","stat":"cha"},{"name":"performance","stat":"cha"},{"name":"persuasion","stat":"cha"},{"name":"stealth","stat":"dex","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"survival","stat":"wis"}],"damagetypes":[],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[],"languages":[{"name":"Abyssal","speaks":true},{"name":"Goblin","speaks":true},{"name":"Infernal","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":2,"damage":[]}